"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The plt.text() function is used to place text at an arbitrary location of the axes, specified by the coordinates. However, the x-coordinate in this case is a string representing a date ('2013-01-05'), but it should be a datetime object or a number that can be interpreted as a date. The date '2013-01-05' needs to be converted to a datetime object or a matplotlib date number.\",\n  \"patch\": \"17c17\\n< plt.text(\\\"2013-01-05\\\", 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n---\\n> plt.text(datetime.datetime(2013, 1, 5), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n\"\n}"